Class
Description
AbstractMainMenu
AbstractMainMenu provides the common behavior for main menus in the application.
AbstractMenu
AbstractMenu serves as a base class for different menu implementations in the application.
AbstractService<T>
The AbstractService class is a generic abstract class designed to provide a basic interface for service classes which interact with a storage service.
AbstractTable<T>
An abstract class representing a table that maintains a collection of entries.
AbstractTableEntry
Abstract base class for table entries in the Hospital Management System (HMS).
AdminMenu
The AdminMenu class handles the display and execution of menu options specific to the administrator role.
App
Main application class for the Hospital Management System (HMS).
AppointmentInformation
Represents the details of a medical appointment, including the appointment ID, patient ID, doctor ID, appointment time slot, and the status of the appointment.
AppointmentOutcome
The AppointmentOutcome class represents the outcome of an appointment.
AppointmentSchedule
The AppointmentSchedule class is responsible for storing and managing a scheduling matrix which includes information about doctor IDs and their assigned time slots.
AppointmentService
AppointmentService provides functionalities to manage medical appointments.
AppointmentStatus
The AppointmentStatus enum represents the various states an appointment can be in.
AuditLogger
The AuditLogger class provides functionality for logging user actions in a hospital management system.
AuthenticationMenu
AuthenticationMenu is responsible for managing the user authentication flow.
AuthenticationResult
Represents the result of an authentication attempt.
AuthenticationService
The AuthenticationService class provides functionalities for user authentication, user management, and password management.
BloodType
Enum representing different blood types.
Colour
The Colour class provides ANSI escape codes for modifying text colors, styles, and backgrounds in the console.
ContactInformation
The ContactInformation class represents the contact details of a patient, including their phone number, email, and address.
ContactInformationTable
This class represents a table of contact information, providing functionality to manage, format, and render contact entries such as phone numbers and emails.
DoctorMenu
The DoctorMenu class provides a menu interface for doctors to perform various actions related to appointment management, medical record handling, and schedule viewing.
DrugDispensaryService
DrugDispensaryService is responsible for managing drug inventory and processing drug dispense and replenish requests.
DrugDispenseRequest
Represents a request to dispense a specific drug with a defined quantity and status.
DrugInventoryEntry
The DrugInventoryEntry class represents an entry in a drug inventory table.
DrugInventoryTable
DrugInventoryTable is a specialized implementation of AbstractTable for managing drug inventory entries.
DrugReplenishRequest
Represents a request to replenish a specific drug with a specified quantity and optional notes.
DrugReplenishRequestTable
Represents a table for managing and storing drug replenish requests.
DrugRequestStatus
Represents the status of a drug request in the dispensary system.
IAppointmentDataInterface
Interface representing the data management operations for appointments.
IDataInterface
Intentionally Empty - specific Services should extend this to define the storage methods needed
IDrugStockDataInterface
Interface defining methods to interact with drug stock data in a healthcare management system.
IMedicalDataInterface
This interface should be implemented by StorageService.
IStaffManagementDataInterface
IStaffManagementDataInterface defines the methods required for managing staff data, including adding, updating, retrieving, and searching for staff members.
LoginAttemptTracker
This class is responsible for tracking login attempts and managing account lockouts.
Main
Main class to start the Hospital Management System (HMS) application.
MedicalEntry
The MedicalEntry class represents a record of a medical consultation which includes details such as patient ID, doctor ID, date of consultation, diagnosis, treatment plan, and consultation notes.
MedicalRecord
This class represents a medical record which contains a collection of medical entries.
MedicalRecordService
MedicalRecordService is responsible for managing medical records, personal particulars, and contact information related to patients in the system.
PasswordMigrationUtil
Utility class for migrating passwords stored in a CSV file.
PasswordUtils
Utility class for password-related operations including hashing and validation.
PatientContext
The PatientContext class extends the UserContext to provide additional context specific to a patient by incorporating a patientID.
PatientMenu
The PatientMenu class represents the main menu for a Patient user.
PatientParticulars
The PatientParticulars class represents the details of a patient, including their ID, name, date of birth, gender, and blood type.
PatientTable
The PatientTable class extends AbstractTable to provide a specialized table for patient particulars.
Person
The Person class represents an individual with a staff ID.
PharmacistMenu
PharmacistMenu class is a view class that displays the main menu for the pharmacist user.
Staff
The Staff class represents a staff member with relevant details, such as staff ID, age, name, role, status, and gender.
StaffManagementService
StaffManagementService provides a set of operations for managing staff members, including adding, updating, removing, searching, and changing staff details and roles.
StaffTable
The StaffTable class extends the AbstractTable class to manage staff data, specifically providing functionality to save to and load from a CSV file.
StorageService
The StorageService class manages the storage and retrieval of various healthcare data tables.
User
Represents a user within the system, encapsulating user-related information such as the user's ID, password, role, and login status.
UserContext
The UserContext class provides a context containing essential user information.
UserRole
Enum representing various roles a user can have within a system.
